post_text:
Some things to remember to keep everyone healthy!
1. Each student should have a fresh, clean mask, each day.
2. Students should bath or shower each day, wearing fresh clothes to school.
3. A healthy diet with fruit, vegetables and vitamins (especially C&D) boosts immune systems.
4. Practice hand washing and mask wearing with younger students.

Hi parents! A couple of quick things.
1. Please make sure students have a fresh face covering each day.
2. Kindergarten parents, if you're able, shoes without laces would really help.
3. No backpacks. Only a small purse or fanny pack.
4. Please schedule your visits to the office.
5. At this time, please do not send treats for parties and birthdays. We will make a big deal out of your child's birthday, but again we need to limit outside " things" entering the building.
6. It is vital that we have updated phone numbers and you are attached to social media and DoJo.
💛💙💛💙💛💙💛💙💛💙💛💙

Enrollment Contest #3! Now through Monday, June 15th.
Anyone who turns in a completed enrollment application OR refers a student that completes an enrollment application will be entered into a drawing to win a BASKET FULL OF CLEANING SUPPLIES! Bonus entry for turning in all paperwork with application (current proof of residence and birth certificate). You'll get one entry for every new student you refer!

As you can see from our recent posts, Stark students SOAR all the way to the finish line- graduation is possible no matter what has happened along the way 🎓❤️
Message us or call this week to enroll! 234.214.4140
Please share!

post_text:
“To me, kindness is choosing to be good to someone. It is choosing to share a compliment, a smile, a laugh, or a moment of goodness with another human. Even if they never return the gesture, it is extending decency, love, and goodness to the world around you. It is splashing every person you meet with a bit of love, with no expectation of receiving it back.”
Ms Heade, 7th Grade.

post_text: Great opportunity.
shared_text:
Officer LaMar Sharpe
February 18 at 1:40 PM ·

This Saturday February 22nd, I will have openings for the Youth Reality Tour. This tour is to help correct current problematic issues within our youth and direct them away from a life behind bars. Youth must be between the ages 10-17 years old. Send me a message or email me at lamar.sharpe@cantonohio.gov to set up an appointment. Limited spots available and once available spots are filled, registration will be closed. #saveouryouth #youthrealitytour
